    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen a language server issues `window/showMessageRequest`, LSP uses `vim.ui.select`. When there are no choices supplied, that just opens a \"Press Enter\" interaction. Maybe such LSes should use `window/showMessage` instead or something, but until every LS is fixed, it would be nice if LSP did the Right Thing\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIdeally, `showMessageRequest` with no options should be treated as if it were a `showMessage` (i.e. `vim.notify` not `vim.ui.select`)",
